Working with folders and files

 FOLDERS ...
 
 md - make directory
 
 > md c:\Timmy
 > md c:\Timmy\Tammy
 
 shortcut
 
 > cd Timmy
 > md Freddy (dont have to make the directory
 
 rd - remove directory
 
 > rd Tammy
 > rd Freddy
 > cd ..
 > rd Timmy
 
 FILES ...
 
 > d: (USB)
 > c: (bring you back where you were)
 
 Copy syntax - copy [source] [destination]
 
 > copy filename1 d:
 > d:
 > dir
 
 DEL and ERASE are syntax to delete
 
 > d:
 > del filename1
 
 copy all .doc
 
 > copy *.doc d:
 * - is a wildcard that means any and all characters
 
 > del *.doc
 
 MOVE syntax
 
 > move *.* d:
 *.* - move evrything
 
 > copy *.* c:\users\studio\documents
 
 REVIEW
	> Use MD and RD to create and remove directories
	> use copy to duplicates files to a new directory or drive,
	use move when you want to remove them from the source directory
	> use del or erase to delete files.
 